Description: Fragment of double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; dull white slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and club symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Minnion; see the Lexicon of Greek Personal Names 1. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 163, 23 or 181, 30?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0122)
